 </disp-formula>where C
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub> is concentration of each toxic metal 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>, and X
 <sub class="sub">a</sub>, X
 <sub class="sub">c</sub> and X
 <sub class="sub">p</sub> are threshold concentrations of toxic metal indicating enrichment, low pollution intensity, and high pollution intensity, respectively. Methods for estimations of X
 <sub class="sub">a</sub>, X
 <sub class="sub">c</sub> and X
 <sub class="sub">p</sub> are explained in Table (
 <xref rid="Tab1" ref-type="table" class="xref">1</xref>). Then, the PI was categorized as follow: non-polluted for PI &lt; 1, low pollution level (1 &lt; PI &lt; 2), moderate level of pollution (2 &lt; PI &lt; 3), and high pollution level (PI &gt; 3)
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR4" class="xref">4</xref>
 </sup>:
</p>
